        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### What’s clinically used?\nAmong ligands identifiable in SRD‑46 Pb²⁺ records:\n\n| Ligand | Present for Pb²⁺ in SRD‑46? | Clinical relevance |\n|---|---|---|\n| **EDTA** | **Yes** | **Yes** — relevant to lead chelation as **calcium disodium EDTA (CaNa2EDTA)** |\n| **DTPA** | **Yes** | Used mainly for certain transuranics, **not standard for lead** |\n| **Penicillamine** | **Yes** | Has clinical history, but not standard first-line modern therapy for lead |\n| **DMSA (succimer)** | Not found in the retrieved Pb²⁺ SRD‑46 set | **Yes clinically**, especially common modern oral lead chelator |\n| **DMPS** | Not found in the retrieved Pb²⁺ SRD‑46 set | Clinical/regional use for some metals, not standard lead first-line everywhere |\n| **BAL (dimercaprol)** | Not found in the retrieved Pb²⁺ SRD‑46 set | Historically used, usually in specific severe scenarios with EDTA |",
