        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "### Bottom line\n| Question | Answer |\n|---|---|\n| Highest-affinity Pb²⁺ ligands in this database? | Mostly **CDTA, DTPA, EDTA, related aminocarboxylates, and some macrocycles** under reported aqueous conditions |\n| Any used clinically? | **Yes: EDTA** clearly; **penicillamine** appears but is less standard. Important clinical chelators like **succimer (DMSA)** are clinically used but were **not retrieved in the Pb²⁺ SRD‑46 records examined** |\n\nA useful chemistry takeaway is that the **largest intrinsic logβ values do not automatically identify the best drug**. Clinical chelation also depends on **toxicity, selectivity, route of administration, and conditional binding at physiologic pH**, which is why **CaNa2EDTA and succimer** remain clinically important even though exotic macrocycles may bind Pb²⁺ very strongly in equilibrium datasets.\n\n**Source:** NIST SRD‑46 equilibrium/stability records for **Pb²⁺ (metal_125)**.",
